    <section id="about">
        <h2>What is Investment Banking?</h2>
        <p>Investment banking involves helping companies raise capital, advising on mergers and acquisitions, and providing financial analysis.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="how-to-become">
        <h2>How to Become an Investment Banker</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Obtain a bachelor's degree in finance, economics, or related fields.</li>
            <li>Internships and networking are essential.</li>
            <li>Obtain an MBA or advanced certifications like CFA.</li>
            <li>Gain experience in financial analysis and corporate finance.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="colleges">
        <h2>Top Colleges for Investment Banking</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Harvard University</li>
            <li>University of Pennsylvania (Wharton)</li>
            <li>Columbia University</li>
            <li>New York University (Stern)</li>
            <li>Stanford University</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="salary">
        <h2>Investment Banking Salary</h2>
        <p>Entry-level salary: $100,000 - $150,000/year</p>
        <p>Mid-level salary: $200,000 - $400,000/year</p>
        <p>Senior-level salary: $500,000 and beyond</p>
    </section>

    <section id="characteristics">
        <h2>Characteristics of Successful Investment Bankers</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Strong analytical skills</li>
            <li>Excellent communication abilities</li>
            <li>Leadership qualities</li>
            <li>Problem-solving mindset</li>
            <li>High stress tolerance</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

